node.accessibility_caption: Photo by ᴍᴀᴛɪʟᴅᴀ on July 22, 2021. May be an illustration of text that says 'how odd can have တ1। this inside me and to you it's just words -David Foster wallace @crazyheadcomics'.

node.text:
one of my favorite quotes by David Foster Wallace, it resonates with me a lot as a very emotional person, i find myself frustrated that i can’t accurately express all that is inside. being very emotional can be good because it makes it easier to relate to other people, but i also think it can be very lonely and overwhelming, especially when the feelings are so big and vast and complex that there aren’t enough words to explain them. feel like this quote also really sums up the experience of being mentally ill and not finding the words to make others understand 

#mentalhealth #crazyheadcomics

node.text:
the years i lived with social anxiety disorder were the years that felt smallest to me, like the world was shrinking as the list of things i avoided grew bigger. it really took away my voice and all of my confidence, i felt so chronically embarrassed, and i HATED being perceived by others because i was convinced that everyone was thinking horrible things about me. it took a LOT of work with my therapist doing CBT and facing all my fears in a safe environment to finally overcome it and be free from social phobia. even though therapy was exhausting and horrifying at times, it was absolutely worth all the hard work ! are you socially anxious or have social anxiety disorder ? what does it look like to you ? 

#mentalhealth #crazyheadcomics #socialanxiety #socialanxietydisorder

node.text:
having something to look forward to is essential for my mental health, even if it’s something small, like having a nice dinner or seeing a friend later that week, it makes my shitty moments feel less permanent. but after the thing has happened, my brain goes off the rails and suddenly i feel like life has no meaning anymore haha, until i find something else to look forward to. i think it’s making it difficult for me to live in the present, this never ending chase for something fun to look forward to. also i build up the things i look forward to so much in my head, that when it happens, it’s disappointing if it’s not as magical as my brain made it out to be. time to focus more on the imperfect now than the potentially perfect-probably not-future 🤠 

#mentalhealth #crazyheadcomics

node.text:
reframing some of the  negative things that i’ve been feeling about myself lately. not lazy, just in need of rest. not difficult, just prioritizing myself, not unlovable, just not everyone’s cup of tea. not stagnant, just growing slowly and steady. 
you gotta question the negative things you think about yourself, because oftentimes, it’s not an accurate portrayal of you, especially if you struggle with low self esteem. and after you question, you gotta replace that thought with a nice thought. until positive thoughts start to become a habit 😌 you are so much better than your anxiety makes you think of yourself ❤️ what’s a negative thing you’ve thought about yourself lately, and how can you reframe it to be more compassionate towards yourself ? 

#mentalheath #crazyheadcomics

node.text:
my TEDx talk is finally up on YouTube, it’s the top link in my bio. when i was offered a talk, i immediately knew what i wanted to talk about. i wanted to criticize the leaders of our world for not taking appropriate measures to help those of us who struggle with mental illness, ESPECIALLY the people who are oppressed and/or impoverished by the capitalist world we sadly live in. i wanted to talk about the importance of mental health education in schools, and the absolute urgency to do something. mental illness and suicide is a global health CRISIS. much like climate change, politicians look the other way. the reason a lot of people are struggling with mental illness, is because the society we live in is in many ways intolerable if you’re not born into privilege. i also wanted to talk a bit about my story and how the mental health stigma has negatively affected me in the work place. this is my first ever public speech and i was the most nervous i’ve ever been, but i proved to myself that i can be anxious and still get shit done. my voice was a bit shaky but i stood tall anyway !!! 
i had to create a whole new life and path for myself because kept entering professional spaces that weren’t accessible for me, for my mental health. a nine to five was impossible for me because of my many mental health diagnoses. i am sick of suffering in silence while trying to fit into places that hurt my health, i just want the world to become accessible for those of us who live with invisible illnesses. i want politicians to do their goddamn job. i want GOOD mental health education in schools. i want free health care for everyone. i want marginalized communities to not be erased in conversation about health. i want change. 

#crazyheadcomics #mentalhealth

node.text:
hi i’m matilda and i live with intense fomo !!!!! my fomo is a bit of a meme in my friend group, my reputation of a fomo-sufferer has started to precede me haha. one time i found out my friends were playing board games together, and even though i HATE board games (it triggers social anxiety for me) i FaceTimed them sobbing and they were like “we didn’t invite you because you hate board games !!!” which in retrospect was very sweet that they knew that about me and was thinking that i wouldn’t have a good time anyway, but i was SHATTERED. like snotty crying and then laughing because i knew i was overreacting and then more crying. my poor friends haha. i feel guilty because i know that my people love me, but when i’m alone it feels like i’ll always be alone 😅 not healthy at all - i also feel a perturbing, everlasting sense of “existential fomo” like i’m missing out on some human experiences that i think other people are having but i’m somehow not. i have a lot of issues with being alone and being co-dependent on other people for happiness. again, not healthy, and i’m working on feeling safe and happy when i’m alone, and i’m also working on remembering that my friends and family and partner care about me even when we’re not together. i also am working on focusing on all the things i have, all the security and safety and joy, instead of the uncertainties and lonely moments in life, and the things i don’t have. i’m trying to confront my fomo so i can be a better friend, and not be so codependent. do you get fomo ??? what do you do to help ?? i was googling about this to research for this post and i honestly didn’t find lots of great advice, so anything would be appreciated !! 

#fomo #fearofmissingout #crazyheadcomics #mentalhealth #anxiety

node.text:
my most requested subject to talk about on here has always been BPD. i think it’s because it’s one of the most stigmatized and misunderstood disorders, there’s a lot of really disgusting misinformation about BPD circling around, how those who live with BPD are dangerous or crazy and need to be avoided. a lot of therapists don’t even have the proper training to deal with patients with bpd. it’s so demonized, it makes me sad :( people with borderline aren’t a lost cause, there’s treatments and coping strategies, bpd traits are manageable if you get the proper support. bpd is treatable !! hugs to all my bpd pals, what does bpd look like to you ??

#bpd #borderlinepersonalitydisorder #mentalhealth #crazyheadcomics
